From: Daniel Stenberg <daniel@haxx.se>
Date: Tue, 4 Mar 2025 23:45:02 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] Negotiate: fix wrong connection reuse

Fix CVE-2026-1965: When asked to do a Negotiate-authenticated request,
libcurl could reuse an existing connection to the same server that was
already authenticated with different credentials.

Bug: https://curl.se/docs/CVE-2026-1965.html
Upstream: https://github.com/curl/curl/commit/34fa034d9a390c4bd65e2d05262755ec8646ac12
---
 lib/url.c | 17 +++++++++++++++--
 1 file changed, 15 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

--- a/lib/url.c
+++ b/lib/url.c
@@ -626,8 +626,21 @@ Curl_addrinfo *Curl_getaddrinfo(struct Curl_easy *data,
    different otherwise we cannot be sure the connection is reusable. */
 static bool negotiate_auth_may_reuse(struct Curl_easy *data,
                                      struct connectdata *conn,
-                                     struct negotiatedata *nego)
+                                     struct negotiatedata *nego,
+                                     struct negotiatedata *proxy_nego)
 {
+  /* if the previous connection was authenticated with Negotiate and the
+     new request also uses Negotiate, make sure we use the same credentials
+     or we might use the wrong connection */
+  if(nego->context) {
+    /* this connection already has a Negotiate context */
+    if(proxy_nego->context) {
+      /* proxy authentication already done */
+      if(strcmp(nego->token, proxy_nego->token))
+        return FALSE;
+    }
+  }
+  
   (void)data;
   (void)conn;
   return TRUE;
